<document>
    <properties>
        <title>Forge Breadcrumb Plugins - How to install</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
      <section name="How to install Breadcrumb Plugin">
      <subsection name="Prerequisites">
        <p>
          These instructions assume that you have an Hippo project based on the Hippo Archetype 7.9.1, i.e.
          a Maven multiproject consisting of at least three submodules: cms, site and content.
        </p>
      </subsection>

      <subsection name="Installation in Site">
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>Add plugin version to the main pom.xml of the project</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
            <forge.breadcrumb.version>1.02.02</forge.breadcrumb.version>
            ]]></source>
            <p><b>Note:</b> always check for the latest version number and compatibility with the project</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Add the following dependency to the site pom.xml of the project</p>
            <source>
              <![CDATA[
          <dependency>
            <groupId>org.onehippo.forge</groupId>
            <artifactId>breadcrumb</artifactId>
            <version>${forge.breadcrumb.version}</version>
          </dependency>]]>
            </source>
            <p><b>Note:</b> always check for the latest version number and compatibility with the Site</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Rebuild your project using Maven and go to <a href="configuration.html">configuration</a>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
      </section>
    </body>
</document>